{"name": "piexif", "metadata": {"name": "piexif", "version": "1.1.3", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: IronPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy", "Topic :: Multimedia", "Topic :: Printing"], "home_page": "https://github.com/hMatoba/Piexif", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "To simplify exif manipulations with python. Writing, reading, and more...", "upload_time": 1561995800}, "documentation": ["---\nsubstitutions:\n  Build Status: |-\n    ```{image} https://api.travis-ci.org/hMatoba/Piexif.svg?branch=master\n    :target: https://travis-ci.org/hMatoba/Piexif\n    ```\n  Coverage Status: |-\n    ```{image} https://coveralls.io/repos/hMatoba/Piexif/badge.svg?branch=master\n    :target: https://coveralls.io/r/hMatoba/Piexif?branch=master\n    ```\n  Windows Build: |-\n    ```{image} https://ci.appveyor.com/api/projects/status/github/hMatoba/Piexif?branch=master&svg=true\n    :target: https://ci.appveyor.com/project/hMatoba/piexif\n    ```\n  docs: |-\n    ```{image} https://readthedocs.org/projects/piexif/badge/?version=latest\n    :target: https://readthedocs.org/projects/piexif/\n    ```\n---\n\n# Piexif\n\n{{ Build Status }} {{ Windows Build }} {{ Coverage Status }} {{ docs }}\n\nTo simplify exif manipulations with Python. Writing, reading, and more... Piexif is pure Python. To everywhere with Python.\n\nDocument: <http://piexif.readthedocs.org/en/latest/>\n\nOnline demo: <http://piexif-demo.appspot.com/demo>\n\n## Install\n\n'easy_install':\n\n```\n$ easy_install piexif\n```\n\nor 'pip':\n\n```\n$ pip install piexif\n```\n\nor download .zip, extract it. Put 'piexif' directory into your environment.\n\n## Why Choose Piexif\n\n- Pure Python. So, it runs everywhere where Python runs.\n- Easy exif manipulations. Read, write, remove...\n- Documented. <http://piexif.readthedocs.org/en/latest/>\n\n## How to Use\n\nThere are only just five functions.\n\n- *load(filename)* - Get exif data as *dict*.\n- *dump(exif_dict)* - Get exif as *bytes*.\n- *insert(exif_bytes, filename)* - Insert exif into JPEG, or WebP.\n- *remove(filename)* - Remove exif from JPEG, or WebP.\n- *transplant(filename, filename)* - Transplant exif from JPEG to JPEG.\n\n## Example\n\n```\nexif_dict = piexif.load(\"foo1.jpg\")\nfor ifd in (\"0th\", \"Exif\", \"GPS\", \"1st\"):\n    for tag in exif_dict[ifd]:\n        print(piexif.TAGS[ifd][tag][\"name\"], exif_dict[ifd][tag])\n```\n\n## With PIL(Pillow)\n\n```\nfrom PIL import Image\nimport piexif\n\nim = Image.open(filename)\nexif_dict = piexif.load(im.info[\"exif\"])\n# process im and exif_dict...\nw, h = im.size\nexif_dict[\"0th\"][piexif.ImageIFD.XResolution] = (w, 1)\nexif_dict[\"0th\"][piexif.ImageIFD.YResolution] = (h, 1)\nexif_bytes = piexif.dump(exif_dict)\nim.save(new_file, \"jpeg\", exif=exif_bytes)\n```\n\n## Environment\n\nTested on Python 2.7, 3.5+ and PyPy3. Piexif would run even on IronPython. Piexif is OS independent and can run on Google App Engine.\n\n## License\n\nThis software is released under the MIT license, see LICENSE.txt.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "piexif._common", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "piexif._common.split_into_segments", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Slices JPEG meta data into a list from JPEG binary data.\n    "]}, {"name": "piexif._common.read_exif_from_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Slices JPEG meta data into a list from JPEG binary data.\n    "]}, {"name": "piexif._common.get_exif_seg", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "segments", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns Exif from JPEG meta data list\n    "]}, {"name": "piexif._common.merge_segments", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "segments", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "exif", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Merges Exif with APP0 and APP1 manipulations.\n    "]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "piexif._remove", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "piexif._remove.remove", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "src", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "new_file", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["py:function:: piexif.remove(filename)\n\nRemove exif from JPEG.\n\n:param str filename: JPEG"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "piexif._dump", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "piexif._dump.dump", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "exif_dict_original", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["py:function:: piexif.load(data)\n\nReturn exif as bytes.\n\n```\nparam dict exif\n\nExif data({\"0th\":dict, \"Exif\":dict, \"GPS\":dict, \"Interop\":dict, \"1st\":dict, \"thumbnail\":bytes})\n\nreturn\n\nExif\n\nrtype\n\nbytes\n```\n"]}, {"name": "piexif._dump._get_thumbnail", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "jpeg", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "piexif._dump._pack_byte", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "piexif._dump._pack_signed_byte", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": 